HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 117
BY REPRESENTATIVE TRAVIS JOHNSON
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Ferriday High School boys basketball team on winning the Louisiana High
School Athletic Association 2026 Division IV Non-Select state championship.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize the Ferriday High School boys basketball
team for their outstanding season and to commend the team on winning the Louisiana High
School Athletic Association 2026 Division IV Non-Select state championship; and
WHEREAS, the Ferriday High School Trojans captured the 2026 Division IV Non-
Select state title by defeating East Iberville High School, 59-55, in the championship game
held at Burton Coliseum in Lake Charles; and
WHEREAS, Marcque "BeBe" Terrell was named the MVP of the championship
game after scoring a game-high eighteen points, grabbing a team-high ten rebounds,
blocking one shot, and dishing out an assist; Caleb Washington facilitated the team's offense
and finished with fourteen points, nine assists, four rebounds, and three steals; and
WHEREAS, Robert Taylor contributed nine points, four rebounds, and two assists;
Demarcus Mitchell finished with seven points, two rebounds, two blocks, and four steals,
and Shavaris Watson added seven points, four rebounds, two steals, two assists, and one
block; and
WHEREAS, Head Coach Shawn Davis led the team to a District 2-2A title and an
undefeated record in district play, and the talented Trojans squad earned the top-seeded
position in the Division IV Non-Select playoff bracket; he is a former standout Ferriday
basketball player who helped lead the program to a state championship victory in 1989; and
WHEREAS, Coach Davis and the members of the Ferriday High School Trojans
basketball team are most deserving of the highest recognition for their dominant season.
